I noticed your car was tilting left.
Looks like your back tire is flat.

1667
01:53:13,070 --> 01:53:14,196
[Tony grunts]

1668
01:53:16,031 --> 01:53:18,659
Ah... [swears in Italian]

1669
01:53:21,328 --> 01:53:22,872
[Tony sighs]

1670
01:53:24,290 --> 01:53:25,624
[Tony grunts]

1671
01:53:25,666 --> 01:53:27,585
Keep it moving. Keep it moving.

1672
01:53:28,419 --> 01:53:29,754
[Tony grunts]

1673
01:53:29,795 --> 01:53:31,547
[soft ambient music]

1674
01:53:31,589 --> 01:53:33,299
[Tony sighs]

1675
01:53:36,886 --> 01:53:38,012
[Tony grunts]

1676
01:53:41,557 --> 01:53:44,977
Okay, be careful, gentlemen.
Merry Christmas.

1677
01:53:45,019 --> 01:53:48,314
-Merry Christmas.
-Thanks, Officer.

1678
01:53:48,355 --> 01:53:50,149
[engine starts]

1679
01:53:52,443 --> 01:53:54,028
[both chuckle]

1680
01:53:56,739 --> 01:53:59,325
[music fades out]

1681
01:54:00,618 --> 01:54:03,245
[radio] <i>Weather advisory warning
this Christmas Eve</i>

1682
01:54:03,287 --> 01:54:06,040
<i>as a major snowstorm
is hitting the Eastern Seaboard</i>

1683
01:54:06,082 --> 01:54:09,043
<i>with the severest weather
in eastern Pennsylvania,</i>

1684
01:54:09,085 --> 01:54:11,962
<i>northern New Jersey
and the five boroughs.</i>

1685
01:54:12,004 --> 01:54:14,882
<i>Travelers are advised to stay
off the New Jersey Turnpike.</i>

1686
01:54:14,924 --> 01:54:19,720
[Tony] All right, that's it. We're done.
I'm pulling us into the next motel.

1687
01:54:20,554 --> 01:54:22,807
Keep going as long as you can, Tony.

1688
01:54:22,848 --> 01:54:26,727
I can't keep my eyes open.
I'm getting hypnotized here.

1689
01:54:27,520 --> 01:54:29,647
Think my brain's gonna explode.

1690
01:54:32,274 --> 01:54:35,402
Hey, we gave it a shot, Doc.

1691
01:54:36,904 --> 01:54:38,197
What are you gonna do?

1692
01:54:39,448 --> 01:54:41,909
[Frank Sinatra] <i>♪ Have yourself </i>♪

1693
01:54:42,660 --> 01:54:45,871
<i>♪ A merry little Christmas... </i>♪

1694
01:54:46,747 --> 01:54:50,543
All right, the table is set, ladies and
gentlemen. Don't run in the house!

1695
01:54:50,584 --> 01:54:52,878
[lively chatter]

1696
01:54:55,881 --> 01:54:59,760
-Mom, Frankie won't let me use it.
-Frankie, let Nicky use it!

1697
01:54:59,802 --> 01:55:01,429
<i>♪ Out of sight... </i>♪

1698
01:55:05,599 --> 01:55:07,518
[lively chatter]

1699
01:55:07,560 --> 01:55:10,271
<i>♪ Have yourself... </i>♪

1700
01:55:10,312 --> 01:55:13,232
Kids! Wash your hands.

1701
01:55:15,109 --> 01:55:17,445
<i>♪ Make the Yuletide gay... </i>♪

1702
01:55:17,486 --> 01:55:20,531
-Dee! Do you need help with the calzone?
-No, I'm fine. No.

1703
01:55:20,573 --> 01:55:24,118
All right! It's time to eat!

1704
01:55:24,160 --> 01:55:28,622
<i>♪ Our troubles will be miles away </i>♪

1705
01:55:33,335 --> 01:55:36,881
<i>♪ And have yourself </i>♪

1706
01:55:38,340 --> 01:55:43,512
<i>♪ A merry little Christmas </i>♪

1707
01:55:44,513 --> 01:55:46,307
<i>♪ Now </i>♪

1708
01:55:46,348 --> 01:55:48,768
Tony. Tony, wake up.

1709
01:55:48,809 --> 01:55:50,686
[gasps]

1710
01:55:52,855 --> 01:55:55,232
-You all right?
-You're home.

1711
01:55:55,274 --> 01:55:56,484
Get inside.

1712
01:56:03,365 --> 01:56:04,533
[Tony grunts]

1713
01:56:06,619 --> 01:56:07,745
[closes door]

1714
01:56:12,374 --> 01:56:15,002
-Good night.
-Wait, wait.

1715
01:56:15,044 --> 01:56:17,546
Come... Come up and meet my family.

1716
01:56:21,008 --> 01:56:22,593
Merry Christmas, Tony.

1717
01:56:24,845 --> 01:56:25,930
[Tony] Yeah...

1718
01:56:27,807 --> 01:56:29,225
Merry Christmas.

1719
01:56:29,266 --> 01:56:31,685
[soft ambient music]

1720
01:56:44,657 --> 01:56:48,411
[music fades out]

1721
01:56:48,452 --> 01:56:50,704
[music and lively chatter]

1722
01:56:50,746 --> 01:56:52,957
[woman]
Hey! You're gonna choke on the bone.

1723
01:56:52,998 --> 01:56:56,210
-I'm just getting started over here.
-[lively chatter]

1724
01:56:56,252 --> 01:56:58,129
-You got it? You got it.
-I got it.

1725
01:56:58,170 --> 01:57:01,465
-Dolores, do you need any help?
-No, no, honey.

1726
01:57:01,507 --> 01:57:03,467
-Not while I'm eating!
-Go ahead.

1727
01:57:03,509 --> 01:57:05,719
-You're not gonna smoke...
-[Tony singing in Italian]

1728
01:57:05,761 --> 01:57:09,306
-[cheering]
-Look who it is! Shakespeare's home! Hey!

1729
01:57:09,348 --> 01:57:10,391
Dad!

1730
01:57:11,434 --> 01:57:13,561
[Tony continues singing]

1731
01:57:13,602 --> 01:57:17,982
-[Tony] Hey. [kisses] How are you?
-[excited chatter]

1732
01:57:18,023 --> 01:57:20,693
-You made it back!
-Hey, Pop. Mwah! Hey!

1733
01:57:20,734 --> 01:57:22,361
-Merry Christmas.
-Merry Christmas.

1734
01:57:22,403 --> 01:57:23,946
-<i>Buon Natale</i>.
-Tony, God bless.

1735
01:57:23,988 --> 01:57:25,448
-Hey.
-Glad you made it back.

1736
01:57:25,489 --> 01:57:27,825
[chatter continues]

1737
01:57:29,785 --> 01:57:32,079
[man] Wonderful, wonderful!

1738
01:57:32,121 --> 01:57:33,706
[man whoops]

1739
01:57:35,583 --> 01:57:37,543
-Yay!
-Ah.

1740
01:57:37,585 --> 01:57:39,086
You hungry?

1741
01:57:39,128 --> 01:57:41,005
-I'm starving.
-All right. Sit down.

1742
01:57:41,839 --> 01:57:44,633
Anything left? [chuckles] Let's go!

1743
01:57:44,675 --> 01:57:46,969
[wind whistling softly]

1744
01:57:57,062 --> 01:58:00,024
-Welcome home, Dr Shirley.
-Thank you, Amit.

1745
01:58:00,065 --> 01:58:03,527
I turned down your bed, sir.
Uh, shall I unpack your luggage now?

1746
01:58:03,569 --> 01:58:06,530
No, no. Please, go home to your family.

1747
01:58:07,615 --> 01:58:08,699
Thank you, sir.

1748
01:58:14,413 --> 01:58:17,166
-Merry Christmas, sir.
-Merry Christmas.

1749
01:58:24,590 --> 01:58:26,884
[clock ticking]

1750
01:58:38,312 --> 01:58:41,482
[silence]

1751
01:58:49,073 --> 01:58:51,992
[soft ambient music]

1752
01:58:54,245 --> 01:58:57,415
[sighs]

1753
01:59:04,588 --> 01:59:07,383
[music fades out]

1754
01:59:08,467 --> 01:59:11,303
<i>♪ Santa Claus is coming... </i>♪

1755
01:59:11,345 --> 01:59:13,472
[lively chatter]

1756
01:59:13,514 --> 01:59:16,267
-Always with the kissing.
-[both laugh]

1757
01:59:16,308 --> 01:59:18,519
What? You never kiss me
like that at the table.

1758
01:59:18,561 --> 01:59:21,105
[woman]
Why don't you ever kiss <i>me </i>like that?

1759
01:59:21,147 --> 01:59:23,983
All right, all right, all right,
relax, relax.

1760
01:59:24,024 --> 01:59:26,652
<i>♪ Santa Claus is coming... </i>♪

1761
01:59:27,403 --> 01:59:29,864
So, Tony, you all right?
You seem a little quiet.

1762
